5.17 Implementing Boundary Conditions
Essential (Dirichlet) boundary conditions (e.g., \(u(0) = u^*\)):
\[\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 & \ldots & \ldots & 0 \\
K_{21} & K_{22} & \ldots & \ldots & K_{2N} \\
\vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots & \vdots \\
K_{N1} & K_{N2} & \ldots & \ldots & K_{NN}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
a_1 \\ a_2 \\ \vdots \\ a_N
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
u^* \\ F_2 \\ \vdots \\ F_N + \ldots
\end{bmatrix}\]

9.5 Weak Form Terms in Master Element Coordinates
We can now write all the terms in the weak form at the element level:
\[\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{K}^e =\int_{\Omega^e} \mathbf{K}(\mathbf{x}(\mathbf{\zeta}))(\mathbf{B}\hat{\phi^e})(\mathbf{F}^T\mathbf{F})^{-1}  (\mathbf{B}\hat{\phi^e})^T \, Jd\hat{\Omega} \\
\mathbf{f}^e = \int_{\Omega^e} \hat{\phi^e}(\mathbf{\zeta})f(\mathbf{x}(\mathbf{\zeta})) \, Jd\hat{\Omega}
\end{aligned}\]
